40|$|We review {{mathematical}} results concerning exponentially small corrections to <b>adiabatic</b> <b>approximations</b> and Born [...] Oppenheimer approximations. Comment: To {{appear in}} {{the proceedings of the}} 2005 International Conference on Differential Equations and Mathematical Physics, University of Alabama, Birmingha...|$|R
40|$|We study a {{one-dimensional}} extended Peierls-Hubbard model {{coupled to}} intracell and intercell phonons for a half-filled band. The calculations are made using the Hartree-Fock and <b>adiabatic</b> <b>approximations</b> for arbitrary temperature. In addition to static spin, charge, and bond density waves, we predict intermediate phases that lack inversion symmetry, and phase transitions that reduce symmetry on increasing temperature...|$|R
40|$|A {{theory for}} the pitch-angle {{scattering}} of cosmic rays in a turbulent magnetic field {{can be derived}} from first principles by applying both the quasi-linear and <b>adiabatic</b> <b>approximations</b> to the master equation for the ensemble averaged distribution function. A proof of the failure of these approximations, taken together, is given. Some predictions of the quasi-linear theory, are given. New wave-like propagation modes have been discovered...|$|R
